					&lt;p&gt;I believe in the U.K. there is one called “Tom Thumb”, basically:&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;ol&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;someone is allocated as the “Thumb Boss”&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;everyone in the group must watch them&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;when they place their thumb on the bar everyone must follow suit. &lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;The last person looses and has to take a good measure of drink. &lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;Usually this person then becomes the “Thumb boss” and they start over.&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;/ol&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;I never found it especially fun, other more subtle games were more entertaining.&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.thirstyswagman.com/2013/01/16/drinking-games/" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;There is a better description available here.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;I would also add there are other games with fingers involved, usually everyone touches the table/bar and the first to move their finger looses etc (basically the reverse).&lt;/p&gt;

				</Text>
